#: ../../../advanced/build_documentation.md:1
msgid "Building documentation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/build_documentation.md:3
msgid ""
"This section outlines how to locally build both the user and developer "
"guides and the C++ API documentation for VTK."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/build_documentation.md:6
msgid "User and developer guides"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/build_documentation.md:8
msgid ""
"VTK's user and developer guides are automatically built and deployed to "
"https://docs.vtk.org every time the `master` branch is updated by leveraging "
"the integration with the _Read the Docs_ service."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/build_documentation.md:12
#: ../../../advanced/build_documentation.md:153
msgid "To locally build the documentation:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/build_documentation.md:0
msgid "Without VTK build tree"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/build_documentation.md:19
#: ../../../advanced/build_documentation.md:157
msgid ""
"[Download](/build_instructions/build.md#obtaining-the-sources) the VTK "
"sources."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/build_documentation.md:21
msgid "Create and activate a virtual environment."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/build_documentation.md:0
msgid "Linux/macOS"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/build_documentation.md:30
msgid ""
"cd Documentation/docs\n"
"\n"
"python3 -m venv .venv\n"
"source .venv/bin/activate\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/build_documentation.md:0
msgid "Windows"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/build_documentation.md:42
msgid ""
"cd Documentation\\docs\n"
"\n"
"py -m venv .venv\n"
".\\.venv\\Scripts\\activate\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/build_documentation.md:49
msgid ""
"`py -m venv` executes venv using the latest Python interpreter you have "
"installed. For more details, read the [Python Windows launcher](https://docs."
"python.org/3/using/windows.html#launcher) docs."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/build_documentation.md:54
msgid "Install dependencies using pip."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/build_documentation.md:63
msgid "python3 -m pip install -r requirements.txt\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/build_documentation.md:72
msgid "py -m pip install -r requirements.txt\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/build_documentation.md:78
msgid "Build the documentation as web pages."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/build_documentation.md:80
msgid "make html\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/build_documentation.md:84
msgid "Open `_build/html/index.html` in a web browser."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/build_documentation.md:0
msgid "Linux"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/build_documentation.md:90
msgid "xdg-open _build/html/index.html\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/build_documentation.md:0
msgid "macOS"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/build_documentation.md:98
msgid "open _build/html/index.html\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/build_documentation.md:108
msgid "start _build\\html\\index.html\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/build_documentation.md:0
msgid "With VTK build tree"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/build_documentation.md:120
msgid ""
"In order to successfully build the VTK documentation using the instructions "
"below, you will need to install the required Python packages."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/build_documentation.md:123
msgid ""
"To ensure that you have the correct dependencies installed in the Python "
"environment associated with the VTK build tree, please run `pip install -r "
"Documentation\\docs\\requirements.txt` or `pip install --user -r "
"Documentation\\docs\\requirements.txt`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/build_documentation.md:127
msgid ""
"If updating your system installation of Python is not feasible or you prefer "
"not to do so, we recommend following the `Without VTK build tree` approach "
"instead."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/build_documentation.md:131
msgid ""
"[Download](/build_instructions/build.md#obtaining-the-sources) VTK sources."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/build_documentation.md:133
msgid ""
"[Configure](/build_instructions/build.md#configure) VTK by setting the "
"`VTK_BUILD_SPHINX_DOCUMENTATION` option to `ON`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/build_documentation.md:136
msgid "Build the `SphinxDoc` target."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/build_documentation.md:141
msgid ""
"Automatic build of preview documentation each time a merge request is "
"submitted is not yet supported due to [limitation](https://docs.readthedocs."
"io/en/stable/guides/pull-requests.html#limitations) of the _Read The Docs_ "
"service that does not yet support self-hosted GitLab deployment."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/build_documentation.md:145
msgid ""
"Solutions to address this are being discussed in https://github.com/"
"readthedocs/readthedocs.org/issues/9464."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/build_documentation.md:148
msgid "C++ API documentation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/build_documentation.md:150
msgid ""
"The C++ API documentation is built and uploaded to https://vtk.org/doc/"
"nightly/html/index.html when the `master` branch is updated."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/build_documentation.md:155
msgid "Install Doxygen"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/build_documentation.md:159
msgid ""
"[Configure](/build_instructions/build.md#configure) VTK by setting the "
"`VTK_BUILD_DOCUMENTATION` option to `ON`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/build_documentation.md:161
msgid "Build the `DoxygenDoc` target."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/build_documentation.md:163
msgid "Targets"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/build_documentation.md:165
msgid ""
"After configuring the VTK using CMake, the following targets may be used to "
"build documentation for VTK:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/build_documentation.md:168
msgid ""
"`DoxygenDoc` - build the doxygen documentation from VTK's C++ source files "
"(`VTK_BUILD_DOCUMENTATION` needs to be `ON` for the target to exist)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/build_documentation.md:170
msgid ""
"`SphinxDoc` - build the sphinx documentation for VTK. "
"(`VTK_BUILD_SPHINX_DOCUMENTATION` needs to be `ON` for the target to exist)."
msgstr ""
